==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iguanodon
<hw>I*gua"no*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iguana</ets> + Gr. <?/, <?/, a tooth.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of gigantic herbivorous dinosaurs
having a birdlike pelvis and large hind legs with three-toed feet
capable of supporting the entire body. Its teeth resemble those of the
iguana, whence its name. Several species are known, mostly from the
Wealden of England and Europe. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iguanodont</ent>⟦br⟧
